ZH: 外面太冷了，我冻住了。
EN: It's too cold outside, I am freezing.
ZH: 穿得太少，容易冻住。
EN: If you don't wear enough, you will easily freeze.
ZH: 冬天的寒风吹得我的手冻住了。
EN: The cold wind in winter froze my hands.
ZH: 孩子站在大雪中玩耍，冻住了脚。
EN: The child stood and played in the snow, freezing his feet.
ZH: 如果你在户外玩耍，别忘了穿厚一点，以免冻住。
EN: If you play outdoors, don't forget to wear thick clothes to prevent freezing.
ZH: 我们在等了很久的公交车里冻住了。
EN: We froze while waiting for the bus for a long time.
ZH: 这个冬天太冷了，简直让人冻住了心。
EN: This winter is so cold, it's freezing my heart.
ZH: 我的手指冻住了，动都动不了。
EN: My fingers are frozen, I can't even move them.
ZH: 外面冰天雪地，谁愿意冻住在室外？
EN: It's icy and snowy outside, who would want to freeze outside?
ZH: 在这样的天气下，要多注意保暖，别冻住了。
EN: In such weather, pay more attention to keep warm and don't freeze.
ZH: 如果你在户外工作，要做好防寒措施，免得冻住。
EN: If you work outdoors, take measures to keep warm to avoid getting frozen.
ZH: 冻住的水管很容易破裂。
EN: Frozen pipes are prone to bursting.
ZH: 冬天在户外要注意保护皮肤，以免冻住。
EN: In winter, it's important to protect your skin outdoors to prevent freezing.
ZH: 冻住的雨水变成了冰。
EN: The freezing rain turned into ice.
ZH: 冻住的湖面上结了一层薄冰。
EN: A thin layer of ice formed on the frozen lake surface.
ZH: 冻住的花朵凋谢了。
EN: The frozen flowers withered.
ZH: 冻住的土地上结了厚厚的雪。
EN: Thick snow formed on the frozen ground.
ZH: 冻住的土壤很难耕种。
EN: It's difficult to cultivate frozen soil.
ZH: 冻住的河面上滑了一层冰。
EN: A layer of ice formed on the frozen river surface.
ZH: 冻住的机器不能正常工作。
EN: Machines that are frozen cannot work properly.
